WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.445 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.445 --> 00:00:07.425 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:07.425 --> 00:00:27.677 align:middle line:90%


00:00:27.677 --> 00:00:29.760 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: Throughout
history the question

00:00:29.760 --> 00:00:33.270 align:middle line:10%
has risen about the missing two
decades in the life of Jesus.

00:00:33.270 --> 00:00:35.850 align:middle line:84%
Many have speculated that
he journeyed east to become

00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:38.260 align:middle line:90%
educated by eastern mystics.

00:00:38.260 --> 00:00:39.870 align:middle line:84%
Paul Davids is
here with us today

00:00:39.870 --> 00:00:42.460 align:middle line:84%
to speak about his
film "Jesus in India,"

00:00:42.460 --> 00:00:44.400 align:middle line:84%
which gives a fascinating
glimpse into some

00:00:44.400 --> 00:00:47.850 align:middle line:84%
of the alleged evidence that
Jesus was indeed in India where

00:00:47.850 --> 00:00:49.650 align:middle line:90%
he is still revered today.

00:00:49.650 --> 00:00:52.250 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's one of the
things people would be probably

00:00:52.250 --> 00:00:56.410 align:middle line:84%
most surprised about is to hear
that the being known as Jesus

00:00:56.410 --> 00:00:58.932 align:middle line:84%
is indeed revered in
India, in Kashmir.

00:00:58.932 --> 00:01:00.140 align:middle line:90%
And we're going to get to it.

00:01:00.140 --> 00:01:04.140 align:middle line:84%
There's even a Pakistani beer
that's involved in this story.

00:01:04.140 --> 00:01:06.700 align:middle line:84%
So before we get going,
I'd like to find out first

00:01:06.700 --> 00:01:09.140 align:middle line:84%
why you decided to
take this project on.

00:01:09.140 --> 00:01:12.050 align:middle line:84%
And then give us a little bit
of the story of Ed Martin,

00:01:12.050 --> 00:01:14.240 align:middle line:84%
who we're going to be
seeing featured quite a bit

00:01:14.240 --> 00:01:18.850 align:middle line:84%
here, which is-- he seems like
such an earnest gentleman that

00:01:18.850 --> 00:01:21.120 align:middle line:84%
was really on a soul
searching journey.

00:01:21.120 --> 00:01:22.250 align:middle line:90%
So set us up.

00:01:22.250 --> 00:01:24.770 align:middle line:10%
>>PAUL DAVIDS: Well, that's
all absolutely true about Ed.

00:01:24.770 --> 00:01:27.900 align:middle line:10%
He's one of the most remarkable
people I've ever met.

00:01:27.900 --> 00:01:30.690 align:middle line:10%
And this was one of the
most challenging movies,

00:01:30.690 --> 00:01:32.620 align:middle line:10%
challenging projects
I've ever taken on.

00:01:32.620 --> 00:01:33.420 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: How so?

00:01:33.420 --> 00:01:38.500 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Because it involved
4,000 miles of travel in India

00:01:38.500 --> 00:01:39.794 align:middle line:90%
under harrowing conditions.

00:01:39.794 --> 00:01:40.960 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It looked like it.

00:01:40.960 --> 00:01:43.840 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Going to
absolutely incredible places,

00:01:43.840 --> 00:01:48.420 align:middle line:84%
ancient temples of the Hindus,
Buddhist temples far up

00:01:48.420 --> 00:01:52.535 align:middle line:84%
in the mountains, meeting
with the Shankaracharya,

00:01:52.535 --> 00:01:55.920 align:middle line:84%
he is essentially
the pope of Hinduism.

00:01:55.920 --> 00:01:57.360 align:middle line:84%
And then traveling
to the Vatican

00:01:57.360 --> 00:02:00.250 align:middle line:84%
to get their point of
view about the question.

00:02:00.250 --> 00:02:06.420 align:middle line:84%
The whole issue of the missing
years, the Bible takes Jesus up

00:02:06.420 --> 00:02:12.760 align:middle line:84%
to about the age 13, giving
learned answers in the temple

00:02:12.760 --> 00:02:16.120 align:middle line:84%
to the contemporary wise
men who are so surprised

00:02:16.120 --> 00:02:17.910 align:middle line:90%
with his wisdom.

00:02:17.910 --> 00:02:21.069 align:middle line:84%
And then we have what in
film we call a jump cut.

00:02:21.069 --> 00:02:22.360 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right, what happened.

00:02:22.360 --> 00:02:24.234 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: There's 18
years are not mentioned.

00:02:24.234 --> 00:02:28.080 align:middle line:84%
There's one sentence
in Luke that says

00:02:28.080 --> 00:02:34.150 align:middle line:84%
and Jesus grew in wisdom
and in stature and in favor

00:02:34.150 --> 00:02:35.870 align:middle line:90%
with God and man.

00:02:35.870 --> 00:02:38.762 align:middle line:90%
And that covers 18 years of--

00:02:38.762 --> 00:02:39.970 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's a catch-all.

00:02:39.970 --> 00:02:42.670 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: --one of the
most important personages

00:02:42.670 --> 00:02:44.060 align:middle line:90%
of all of history.

00:02:44.060 --> 00:02:49.430 align:middle line:84%
So the question arises why
is all of that left out.

00:02:49.430 --> 00:02:51.770 align:middle line:84%
Because in the Bible
you next see Jesus

00:02:51.770 --> 00:02:56.670 align:middle line:84%
by the River Jordan being
baptized by his cousin John.

00:02:56.670 --> 00:02:59.860 align:middle line:84%
And it says that Jesus got
to be around 30 years of age

00:02:59.860 --> 00:03:01.540 align:middle line:90%
at that point.

00:03:01.540 --> 00:03:04.270 align:middle line:90%
Now how did I come upon this?

00:03:04.270 --> 00:03:09.730 align:middle line:84%
I met Edward T. Martin
at a conference.

00:03:09.730 --> 00:03:13.760 align:middle line:84%
Actually I think it was
2002 when we first met.

00:03:13.760 --> 00:03:17.950 align:middle line:84%
And he had a book called
"King of Travelers,

00:03:17.950 --> 00:03:20.980 align:middle line:90%
Jesus' Lost Years in India."

00:03:20.980 --> 00:03:22.820 align:middle line:84%
I thought it was
very curious and I

00:03:22.820 --> 00:03:26.660 align:middle line:90%
like curious and unusual topics.

00:03:26.660 --> 00:03:30.700 align:middle line:84%
And he pointed out
to me that there

00:03:30.700 --> 00:03:36.810 align:middle line:84%
is a book of Muslims sayings
that is well known by Muslims

00:03:36.810 --> 00:03:38.500 align:middle line:90%
that refers to Jesus.

00:03:38.500 --> 00:03:40.560 align:middle line:90%
They called him Saint Issa.

00:03:40.560 --> 00:03:44.580 align:middle line:84%
It refers to him as
the king of travelers

00:03:44.580 --> 00:03:47.660 align:middle line:84%
or the prince of
travelers, the concept

00:03:47.660 --> 00:03:50.955 align:middle line:84%
being that he traveled more
than any other contemporary

00:03:50.955 --> 00:03:52.550 align:middle line:90%
of his time.

00:03:52.550 --> 00:03:58.750 align:middle line:84%
He wasn't just in
Galilee and Judea.

00:03:58.750 --> 00:04:03.920 align:middle line:84%
But his journey was to reunite
the lost tribes of Israel.

00:04:03.920 --> 00:04:05.820 align:middle line:84%
And they were
scattered, and many

00:04:05.820 --> 00:04:07.370 align:middle line:90%
were scattered to the east.

00:04:07.370 --> 00:04:09.637 align:middle line:84%
And that included India,
a lot of evidence of this.

00:04:09.637 --> 00:04:11.720 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This is a really
fascinating part, which

00:04:11.720 --> 00:04:13.090 align:middle line:90%
we'll get into further on.

00:04:13.090 --> 00:04:15.320 align:middle line:90%
But I found that fascinating.

00:04:15.320 --> 00:04:17.746 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: But the
relationship with Ed--

00:04:17.746 --> 00:04:19.579 align:middle line:84%
just I'll fill in a
little more because he's

00:04:19.579 --> 00:04:21.829 align:middle line:84%
so important to the
story, in his book.

00:04:21.829 --> 00:04:23.790 align:middle line:90%
He's a mountain climber.

00:04:23.790 --> 00:04:25.090 align:middle line:90%
He's an adventurer.

00:04:25.090 --> 00:04:26.820 align:middle line:90%
He's from Texas.

00:04:26.820 --> 00:04:28.780 align:middle line:90%
He hunts with a bow and arrow.

00:04:28.780 --> 00:04:30.790 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: He's from
fundamentalist country too.

00:04:30.790 --> 00:04:34.200 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: He was raised as a
fundamentalist and he liked it.

00:04:34.200 --> 00:04:36.900 align:middle line:84%
His mother took them to
church three times a week,

00:04:36.900 --> 00:04:39.450 align:middle line:84%
and they were serious
about their churching.

00:04:39.450 --> 00:04:40.450 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes they were.

00:04:40.450 --> 00:04:41.150 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: They liked it.

00:04:41.150 --> 00:04:41.650 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You see
that in the film.

00:04:41.650 --> 00:04:43.090 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: They liked it.

00:04:43.090 --> 00:04:47.270 align:middle line:84%
And his problem with
his Church of Christ

00:04:47.270 --> 00:04:50.840 align:middle line:84%
was that he asked
too many questions.

00:04:50.840 --> 00:04:54.900 align:middle line:84%
They would say Ed why are
you worrying about that.

00:04:54.900 --> 00:04:57.120 align:middle line:84%
You worry about
your own salvation.

00:04:57.120 --> 00:04:59.400 align:middle line:84%
That's what Ed needs
to worry about,

00:04:59.400 --> 00:05:01.730 align:middle line:84%
not where Jesus was
during those 18 years.

00:05:01.730 --> 00:05:04.360 align:middle line:90%
What difference does it make?

00:05:04.360 --> 00:05:07.770 align:middle line:84%
Ed explains in the book that he
came upon this theory of Jesus

00:05:07.770 --> 00:05:11.100 align:middle line:84%
in India from a few
different sources.

00:05:11.100 --> 00:05:12.970 align:middle line:90%
One was Edgar Cayce.

00:05:12.970 --> 00:05:14.577 align:middle line:84%
He joined an Edgar
Cayce study group.

00:05:14.577 --> 00:05:15.910 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That'll get you going.

00:05:15.910 --> 00:05:18.660 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: He found that this
great sleeping prophet had

00:05:18.660 --> 00:05:20.800 align:middle line:90%
said that Jesus was in India.

00:05:20.800 --> 00:05:24.910 align:middle line:84%
Then number two Ed came
across "The Aquarian Gospel

00:05:24.910 --> 00:05:30.880 align:middle line:84%
of Jesus the Christ" by Reverend
Dowling, a civil war writer.

00:05:30.880 --> 00:05:32.720 align:middle line:90%
This was channeled material.

00:05:32.720 --> 00:05:37.040 align:middle line:84%
Again, it said that Jesus spent
part of his life in India.

00:05:37.040 --> 00:05:40.280 align:middle line:84%
And I believe that
does mention Jagannath

00:05:40.280 --> 00:05:44.780 align:middle line:84%
where there was a famous Hindu
temple that's 2,500 years old.

00:05:44.780 --> 00:05:46.930 align:middle line:84%
That temple would've
been there for 500 years

00:05:46.930 --> 00:05:49.490 align:middle line:90%
by the time Jesus showed up.

00:05:49.490 --> 00:05:52.220 align:middle line:84%
So the idea of
going to Jagannath

00:05:52.220 --> 00:05:53.679 align:middle line:84%
and talking to the
head of Hinduism

00:05:53.679 --> 00:05:55.094 align:middle line:84%
and getting his
side of the story.

00:05:55.094 --> 00:05:55.930 align:middle line:90%
I mean we did this.

00:05:55.930 --> 00:05:57.429 align:middle line:90%
We actually did it.

00:05:57.429 --> 00:05:58.720 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I know, it's amazing.

00:05:58.720 --> 00:05:59.980 align:middle line:90%
You really went to the lengths.

00:05:59.980 --> 00:06:00.210 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: We went
to the Dalai Lama.

00:06:00.210 --> 00:06:00.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes you did.

00:06:00.320 --> 00:06:01.230 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: We went
to the Vatican.

00:06:01.230 --> 00:06:01.965 align:middle line:90%
We got to--

00:06:01.965 --> 00:06:02.920 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And we're going
to hear from the Dalai

00:06:02.920 --> 00:06:03.753 align:middle line:90%
Lama in this as well

00:06:03.753 --> 00:06:05.700 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: It was incredible.

00:06:05.700 --> 00:06:09.850 align:middle line:84%
There was a third source
for Ed, the writings

00:06:09.850 --> 00:06:12.590 align:middle line:90%
of Paramahansa Yogananda.

00:06:12.590 --> 00:06:17.662 align:middle line:84%
Yogananda, the great
yogi who brought I think

00:06:17.662 --> 00:06:18.870 align:middle line:90%
responsible for bringing it--

00:06:18.870 --> 00:06:19.840 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: To the
Western world, sure.

00:06:19.840 --> 00:06:21.470 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: --yoga to
the Western world

00:06:21.470 --> 00:06:24.060 align:middle line:84%
and founded the
self-realization fellowship,

00:06:24.060 --> 00:06:27.520 align:middle line:90%
which is very important today.

00:06:27.520 --> 00:06:31.030 align:middle line:84%
Yogananda died in
the early 1950s,

00:06:31.030 --> 00:06:35.030 align:middle line:84%
but his writings such as
"Autobiography of a Yogi,"

00:06:35.030 --> 00:06:39.030 align:middle line:84%
are revered today,
very, very widely read.

00:06:39.030 --> 00:06:43.340 align:middle line:84%
And Yogananda claimed that Jesus
was in India for those-- a lot

00:06:43.340 --> 00:06:44.500 align:middle line:90%
of those missing years.

00:06:44.500 --> 00:06:46.080 align:middle line:84%
We're not saying
the whole 18 years,

00:06:46.080 --> 00:06:49.410 align:middle line:84%
but that he took the
Silk Road to the east.

00:06:49.410 --> 00:06:54.840 align:middle line:84%
Now his explanation was that the
three wise men were from India.

00:06:54.840 --> 00:06:55.720 align:middle line:90%
That's been debated.

00:06:55.720 --> 00:06:56.810 align:middle line:90%
Where were they from?

00:06:56.810 --> 00:06:57.260 align:middle line:90%
Who knows.

00:06:57.260 --> 00:06:57.740 align:middle line:90%
Were they Persians.

00:06:57.740 --> 00:06:58.120 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Some say Persia.

00:06:58.120 --> 00:06:58.920 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, exactly.

00:06:58.920 --> 00:07:00.750 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: Yeah, your Persia.

00:07:00.750 --> 00:07:02.240 align:middle line:90%
Yogananda said no, no, no.

00:07:02.240 --> 00:07:06.420 align:middle line:84%
The gifts were gold,
incense, and myrrh,

00:07:06.420 --> 00:07:11.630 align:middle line:84%
and those were traditional
gifts that Indian holy men would

00:07:11.630 --> 00:07:16.540 align:middle line:90%
bestow upon worthy individuals.

00:07:16.540 --> 00:07:22.180 align:middle line:84%
So he claimed that they had
an influence in Jesus' life

00:07:22.180 --> 00:07:25.380 align:middle line:84%
and he was essentially
repaying the visit.

00:07:25.380 --> 00:07:31.800 align:middle line:84%
And even in the Aquarian gospel
it talks about a Prince Ravanna

00:07:31.800 --> 00:07:34.680 align:middle line:84%
I believe from India who
became a sort of patron.

00:07:34.680 --> 00:07:37.811 align:middle line:90%
Now is any of this true?

00:07:37.811 --> 00:07:39.810 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The point is
these were the influences

00:07:39.810 --> 00:07:41.740 align:middle line:84%
to start him on this
amazing journey.

00:07:41.740 --> 00:07:42.698 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: That's right.

00:07:42.698 --> 00:07:48.339 align:middle line:84%
He started and he
badgered his minister.

00:07:48.339 --> 00:07:49.880 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We're
going to show a clip.

00:07:49.880 --> 00:07:50.840 align:middle line:90%
Do you mind?

00:07:50.840 --> 00:07:51.930 align:middle line:90%
In a moment.

00:07:51.930 --> 00:07:52.971 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: We can do that.

00:07:52.971 --> 00:07:56.490 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We need to
show where Ed came from

00:07:56.490 --> 00:07:58.460 align:middle line:90%
and what he was up against.

00:07:58.460 --> 00:08:00.670 align:middle line:84%
He lost a lot of
credibility, a lot

00:08:00.670 --> 00:08:03.320 align:middle line:84%
of street cred in his community
and certainly with the church,

00:08:03.320 --> 00:08:06.250 align:middle line:84%
and among his family and
so forth for pursuing

00:08:06.250 --> 00:08:09.675 align:middle line:84%
this crazy odyssey to again
uncover these missing years.

00:08:09.675 --> 00:08:11.300 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Regina, he
comes from a world

00:08:11.300 --> 00:08:16.530 align:middle line:84%
of no drinking, no dancing,
three times a week at church.

00:08:16.530 --> 00:08:20.070 align:middle line:84%
So his persistence
after he heard

00:08:20.070 --> 00:08:22.410 align:middle line:84%
about the possibility
of Jesus in India

00:08:22.410 --> 00:08:24.300 align:middle line:84%
got him blackballed
from a church

00:08:24.300 --> 00:08:27.149 align:middle line:84%
that his family had been
members of for their whole life.

00:08:27.149 --> 00:08:28.190 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: His whole life.

00:08:28.190 --> 00:08:31.450 align:middle line:84%
So let's take a look
at the clip of some

00:08:31.450 --> 00:08:35.480 align:middle line:84%
of his former colleagues in
the church and his minister.

00:08:35.480 --> 00:08:36.340 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: Yes.

00:08:36.340 --> 00:08:40.230 align:middle line:10%
>>Well, we're I guess you'd say
fundamental as far as scripture

00:08:40.230 --> 00:08:41.030 align:middle line:10%
is concerned.

00:08:41.030 --> 00:08:43.132 align:middle line:10%
>>We believe every
word of it, yes.

00:08:43.132 --> 00:08:45.215 align:middle line:10%
>>It was understood we
were not supposed to dance.

00:08:45.215 --> 00:08:48.173 align:middle line:10%
We weren't supposed to drink.

00:08:48.173 --> 00:08:50.638 align:middle line:90%
Gambling was a no-no.

00:08:50.638 --> 00:08:56.415 align:middle line:84%
I've known Ed Martin for
I guess 50 years since he

00:08:56.415 --> 00:08:57.540 align:middle line:90%
was a little boy certainly.

00:08:57.540 --> 00:09:00.662 align:middle line:84%
I'm not sure how old Ed
is, but I've known him

00:09:00.662 --> 00:09:02.470 align:middle line:90%
I guess all of his life.

00:09:02.470 --> 00:09:04.935 align:middle line:84%
Ed has always been
out there on the edge.

00:09:04.935 --> 00:09:09.372 align:middle line:84%
The difference between being
a visionary and being crazy

00:09:09.372 --> 00:09:11.837 align:middle line:84%
is a very small
difference sometimes.

00:09:11.837 --> 00:09:16.810 align:middle line:84%
And none of us know-- none of
us know what that difference is.

00:09:16.810 --> 00:09:19.230 align:middle line:84%
Ed's grasp of reality and
mine are not the same thing.

00:09:19.230 --> 00:09:23.548 align:middle line:84%
>>He has always wandered
around and he enjoys traveling.

00:09:23.548 --> 00:09:26.760 align:middle line:10%
And he just never
has settled in.

00:09:26.760 --> 00:09:31.184 align:middle line:84%
And that's all right because
that's what he wants to do.

00:09:31.184 --> 00:09:33.510 align:middle line:84%
But that's not what the
rest of us do of course.

00:09:33.510 --> 00:09:35.962 align:middle line:84%
That's different
is what I'm saying.

00:09:35.962 --> 00:09:38.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Anyway, I think
we can see that what he did

00:09:38.170 --> 00:09:40.044 align:middle line:84%
was quite a departure
from what he came from.

00:09:40.044 --> 00:09:41.550 align:middle line:84%
And I just had
to-- I just wanted

00:09:41.550 --> 00:09:43.510 align:middle line:84%
to show that because it
took a lot of courage

00:09:43.510 --> 00:09:46.910 align:middle line:90%
for him to go on this odyssey.

00:09:46.910 --> 00:09:49.030 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: He risked
everything to pursue the--

00:09:49.030 --> 00:09:50.321 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: He risked everything.

00:09:50.321 --> 00:09:54.840 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Now when he
was young he decided

00:09:54.840 --> 00:09:56.610 align:middle line:90%
to join the Peace Corps.

00:09:56.610 --> 00:10:01.170 align:middle line:84%
It was the early 1970s and
they sent him to Afghanistan.

00:10:01.170 --> 00:10:03.210 align:middle line:90%
He wanted to go to India.

00:10:03.210 --> 00:10:05.270 align:middle line:84%
But he felt that being
in Afghanistan at least

00:10:05.270 --> 00:10:07.660 align:middle line:90%
he would be close to India.

00:10:07.660 --> 00:10:09.630 align:middle line:84%
And so he accepted
that assignment

00:10:09.630 --> 00:10:12.190 align:middle line:84%
to teach English as
a second language.

00:10:12.190 --> 00:10:16.690 align:middle line:84%
And before he
departed his mother

00:10:16.690 --> 00:10:21.040 align:middle line:84%
ran into an old high school
friend who-- they hadn't

00:10:21.040 --> 00:10:22.240 align:middle line:90%
seen each other in years.

00:10:22.240 --> 00:10:25.160 align:middle line:84%
This man had become
a diplomat in India.

00:10:25.160 --> 00:10:29.230 align:middle line:84%
And when she told him
of her son's ambition

00:10:29.230 --> 00:10:31.610 align:middle line:90%
he said I've got to talk to him.

00:10:31.610 --> 00:10:35.460 align:middle line:84%
And the conversation between
this man and Ed was pivotal.

00:10:35.460 --> 00:10:36.802 align:middle line:90%
It was as though it was fated.

00:10:36.802 --> 00:10:38.260 align:middle line:84%
It was one of those
things that had

00:10:38.260 --> 00:10:41.980 align:middle line:84%
to happen because this diplomat
said if you go to India

00:10:41.980 --> 00:10:44.450 align:middle line:90%
you must go to Kashmir.

00:10:44.450 --> 00:10:46.790 align:middle line:84%
And it was Ed's decision
to go to Kashmir

00:10:46.790 --> 00:10:51.130 align:middle line:84%
that opened up for
him an immense part

00:10:51.130 --> 00:10:54.970 align:middle line:84%
of the hidden story
about Jesus in India.

00:10:54.970 --> 00:10:57.690 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: In an area which
since has had so much conflict.

00:10:57.690 --> 00:10:59.810 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to
show a bit of film

00:10:59.810 --> 00:11:02.390 align:middle line:84%
at the end about what
he was up against trying

00:11:02.390 --> 00:11:03.792 align:middle line:90%
to get to the crypt.

00:11:03.792 --> 00:11:05.250 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Regina,
when we decided--

00:11:05.250 --> 00:11:06.130 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You were scared.

00:11:06.130 --> 00:11:06.725 align:middle line:90%
I mean you had--

00:11:06.725 --> 00:11:07.210 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: Yes.

00:11:07.210 --> 00:11:09.740 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --really terrorist
activities following you.

00:11:09.740 --> 00:11:12.510 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: He was there
in his younger years

00:11:12.510 --> 00:11:14.850 align:middle line:90%
during his Afghanistan days.

00:11:14.850 --> 00:11:18.420 align:middle line:84%
But when we were there
with the film crew,

00:11:18.420 --> 00:11:20.180 align:middle line:84%
and I'll say that when
the movie actually

00:11:20.180 --> 00:11:25.847 align:middle line:84%
happened we had a film crew that
was mainly Hindus from India.

00:11:25.847 --> 00:11:28.180 align:middle line:84%
I think there was one Muslim
who helped us, particularly

00:11:28.180 --> 00:11:30.420 align:middle line:84%
in Kashmir, because
Kashmir is divided

00:11:30.420 --> 00:11:33.250 align:middle line:84%
between the Muslims
and the Hindus.

00:11:33.250 --> 00:11:37.050 align:middle line:84%
And there's sort of a
silent war always going on.

00:11:37.050 --> 00:11:40.080 align:middle line:84%
There's soldiers on
every block with rifles.

00:11:40.080 --> 00:11:42.780 align:middle line:84%
And here we work,
two Americans landing

00:11:42.780 --> 00:11:45.850 align:middle line:84%
into that situation at
a time when the State

00:11:45.850 --> 00:11:47.429 align:middle line:90%
Department advised against it.

00:11:47.429 --> 00:11:48.470 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, don't go.

00:11:48.470 --> 00:11:51.029 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: It wasn't
forbidden, but we

00:11:51.029 --> 00:11:52.070 align:middle line:90%
should have known better.

00:11:52.070 --> 00:11:52.903 align:middle line:90%
It was sort of the--

00:11:52.903 --> 00:11:55.340 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, as you say
in the documentary it seemed

00:11:55.340 --> 00:11:57.420 align:middle line:84%
like you were able to
get through each step

00:11:57.420 --> 00:12:00.320 align:middle line:84%
you needed, but within 24
hours some kind of terror

00:12:00.320 --> 00:12:02.440 align:middle line:84%
was following on your
heels in that exact place

00:12:02.440 --> 00:12:03.620 align:middle line:90%
you'd been the day before.

00:12:03.620 --> 00:12:05.940 align:middle line:84%
So it took a lot of courage
for you guys to do this.

00:12:05.940 --> 00:12:07.579 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Regina,
we did feel as if we

00:12:07.579 --> 00:12:08.870 align:middle line:90%
were protected on this journey.

00:12:08.870 --> 00:12:09.890 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:12:09.890 --> 00:12:11.700 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: And to give
you some examples,

00:12:11.700 --> 00:12:19.280 align:middle line:84%
we were going to go to
a famous Krishna temple.

00:12:19.280 --> 00:12:21.820 align:middle line:84%
I forget if it was in the
place of Krishna's birth.

00:12:21.820 --> 00:12:25.790 align:middle line:84%
But we canceled that
part of the trip.

00:12:25.790 --> 00:12:29.240 align:middle line:84%
And there was a terrorist
attack there at that Temple.

00:12:29.240 --> 00:12:31.690 align:middle line:90%
We would have been there.

00:12:31.690 --> 00:12:37.610 align:middle line:84%
And in Kashmir, the
area that we were at,

00:12:37.610 --> 00:12:41.370 align:middle line:84%
there were a number
of people murdered,

00:12:41.370 --> 00:12:44.866 align:middle line:84%
killed within days
of our departure.

00:12:44.866 --> 00:12:46.240 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The
force was with you.

00:12:46.240 --> 00:12:47.573 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: The force was with us.

00:12:47.573 --> 00:12:48.944 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:12:48.944 --> 00:12:51.360 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: We asked for the
blessing of Yogananda before we

00:12:51.360 --> 00:12:51.640 align:middle line:90%
went and--

00:12:51.640 --> 00:12:53.320 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So this
was your own odyssey.

00:12:53.320 --> 00:12:55.380 align:middle line:84%
Now going back to
the life of Jesus

00:12:55.380 --> 00:12:57.120 align:middle line:84%
and what has been
speculated and what

00:12:57.120 --> 00:13:01.140 align:middle line:84%
looks like it may very well
have some historical roots

00:13:01.140 --> 00:13:03.289 align:middle line:84%
that are valid-- that
you have validated.

00:13:03.289 --> 00:13:05.080 align:middle line:84%
I mean to the extent
you could, considering

00:13:05.080 --> 00:13:07.520 align:middle line:84%
you're getting a lot of
resistance out of this.

00:13:07.520 --> 00:13:09.760 align:middle line:90%
You're talking about a young--

00:13:09.760 --> 00:13:12.400 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: We call it a
2,000 year old cold case.

00:13:12.400 --> 00:13:13.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, cold case.

00:13:13.570 --> 00:13:15.280 align:middle line:84%
And so in this cold
case you're talking

00:13:15.280 --> 00:13:18.670 align:middle line:84%
about a young man who
by the age of 12, 13

00:13:18.670 --> 00:13:21.930 align:middle line:84%
his elders were listening to
with reverence, because he was

00:13:21.930 --> 00:13:29.300 align:middle line:84%
speaking such incredibly-- not
just esoteric but sophisticated

00:13:29.300 --> 00:13:32.850 align:middle line:84%
wisdoms beyond his
peers, beyond the sages

00:13:32.850 --> 00:13:34.160 align:middle line:90%
and rabbis of the day.

00:13:34.160 --> 00:13:36.060 align:middle line:90%
So he was a respected young man.

00:13:36.060 --> 00:13:38.570 align:middle line:84%
So of course we already know
he's imbued with something.

00:13:38.570 --> 00:13:41.710 align:middle line:84%
And now it's thought that
he may have taken off

00:13:41.710 --> 00:13:44.675 align:middle line:84%
with a caravan along
the Silk Route.

00:13:44.675 --> 00:13:47.175 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Well, that was the
way to get to the east in those

00:13:47.175 --> 00:13:48.520 align:middle line:90%
days.

00:13:48.520 --> 00:13:51.700 align:middle line:84%
I mean Jerusalem was
a cosmopolitan city.

00:13:51.700 --> 00:13:53.200 align:middle line:84%
There were people
from China there.

00:13:53.200 --> 00:13:53.710 align:middle line:90%
There were people from India.

00:13:53.710 --> 00:13:55.710 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: All kinds of a
trading going on, yeah.

00:13:55.710 --> 00:13:56.986 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: Traders, traders.

00:13:56.986 --> 00:14:01.450 align:middle line:84%
Now in the Jewish tradition
of course he reaches 13.

00:14:01.450 --> 00:14:03.140 align:middle line:84%
He would have been
bar mitzvahed,

00:14:03.140 --> 00:14:07.150 align:middle line:84%
which means you're a man
now and you get married.

00:14:07.150 --> 00:14:10.440 align:middle line:84%
That's the next thing that
happens in those days.

00:14:10.440 --> 00:14:12.620 align:middle line:90%
You're an eligible bachelor.

00:14:12.620 --> 00:14:15.280 align:middle line:84%
They're going to
find a mate for you.

00:14:15.280 --> 00:14:18.390 align:middle line:90%
Well, he didn't marry.

00:14:18.390 --> 00:14:20.700 align:middle line:84%
And that kind of
lends credibility

00:14:20.700 --> 00:14:24.150 align:middle line:84%
to the idea that he
didn't remain there

00:14:24.150 --> 00:14:30.990 align:middle line:84%
but joined a caravan and
departed for the east.

00:14:30.990 --> 00:14:32.880 align:middle line:90%
That's the theory.

00:14:32.880 --> 00:14:36.490 align:middle line:84%
And then the question
is, after 2,000 years,

00:14:36.490 --> 00:14:38.770 align:middle line:84%
and with a little help from
Elizabeth Clare Prophet

00:14:38.770 --> 00:14:42.080 align:middle line:84%
and in her book, "The Lost
Years of"-- and a little help

00:14:42.080 --> 00:14:44.905 align:middle line:84%
from German writer
Holger Kersten,

00:14:44.905 --> 00:14:50.780 align:middle line:84%
"Jesus Lived in
India," can we find

00:14:50.780 --> 00:14:54.130 align:middle line:84%
some pretty convincing evidence
that it really happened.

00:14:54.130 --> 00:14:59.610 align:middle line:84%
And I think that there's a
lot that favors that that we

00:14:59.610 --> 00:15:01.960 align:middle line:90%
can really put on the table.

00:15:01.960 --> 00:15:04.150 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Let's talk
about the Pakistani beer.

00:15:04.150 --> 00:15:05.940 align:middle line:84%
Now we're going to
start with the lowest

00:15:05.940 --> 00:15:09.740 align:middle line:84%
element of culture, which
is having one at happy hour.

00:15:09.740 --> 00:15:11.310 align:middle line:84%
But the name of this
particular beer,

00:15:11.310 --> 00:15:15.670 align:middle line:84%
just to show how deep
a part of the native

00:15:15.670 --> 00:15:20.210 align:middle line:84%
culture the presence
of Issa was.

00:15:20.210 --> 00:15:24.930 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Well yes, I mean but
this beer was called Murree.

00:15:24.930 --> 00:15:25.940 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I understand.

00:15:25.940 --> 00:15:27.356 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: It's a
town in Pakistan.

00:15:27.356 --> 00:15:33.290 align:middle line:84%
It's spelled M-U-R-R-E-E. And
when Ed was in the Peace Corps

00:15:33.290 --> 00:15:37.470 align:middle line:84%
in Afghanistan you
couldn't find liquor there.

00:15:37.470 --> 00:15:38.460 align:middle line:90%
It's a Muslim area.

00:15:38.460 --> 00:15:43.380 align:middle line:84%
But there was a certain American
section where it was allowed

00:15:43.380 --> 00:15:45.030 align:middle line:90%
and you could get a beer.

00:15:45.030 --> 00:15:47.210 align:middle line:84%
And he said he met a
man named Mr. Wilson who

00:15:47.210 --> 00:15:50.510 align:middle line:84%
was the bartender and
he saw this Murree beer.

00:15:50.510 --> 00:15:52.970 align:middle line:84%
And he said, well
that's an English name.

00:15:52.970 --> 00:15:54.360 align:middle line:90%
What's that doing?

00:15:54.360 --> 00:16:00.255 align:middle line:84%
And Mr. Wilson said,
well that's Murree.

00:16:00.255 --> 00:16:01.230 align:middle line:90%
That's Mary.

00:16:01.230 --> 00:16:05.640 align:middle line:84%
That's mother of Jesus, Sahib,
most assuredly mother of Jesus.

00:16:05.640 --> 00:16:06.900 align:middle line:90%
The town named after her.

00:16:06.900 --> 00:16:08.624 align:middle line:90%
She is buried there in Pakistan.

00:16:08.624 --> 00:16:10.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This will
make a lot of people

00:16:10.290 --> 00:16:13.915 align:middle line:84%
upset that think that she
might be up north in England.

00:16:13.915 --> 00:16:15.300 align:middle line:90%
No, no in England.

00:16:15.300 --> 00:16:16.270 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Oh, some
say England and some

00:16:16.270 --> 00:16:16.970 align:middle line:90%
say she ascended bodily.

00:16:16.970 --> 00:16:18.920 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah,
Glastonbury and all, yeah.

00:16:18.920 --> 00:16:20.890 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Well, the
point is he hears a story

00:16:20.890 --> 00:16:22.630 align:middle line:90%
about a tomb in Pakistan.

00:16:22.630 --> 00:16:26.170 align:middle line:84%
Now Suzanne Olsson is a
writer who has investigated

00:16:26.170 --> 00:16:27.570 align:middle line:90%
this very thoroughly.

00:16:27.570 --> 00:16:31.090 align:middle line:84%
She's written books about
it, the tomb of Mary

00:16:31.090 --> 00:16:33.320 align:middle line:90%
in Murree, Pakistan.

00:16:33.320 --> 00:16:36.920 align:middle line:84%
Why would they
possibly believe this?

00:16:36.920 --> 00:16:39.692 align:middle line:84%
This has to do with the second
part of the story really,

00:16:39.692 --> 00:16:41.525 align:middle line:84%
so we're really jumping
ahead here because--

00:16:41.525 --> 00:16:42.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, let's
not jump ahead.

00:16:42.910 --> 00:16:45.201 align:middle line:84%
I just want to say we've got
a beer here that validates

00:16:45.201 --> 00:16:46.150 align:middle line:90%
Jesus was in India OK.

00:16:46.150 --> 00:16:46.800 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: We've got Mary.

00:16:46.800 --> 00:16:47.430 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because
his mother was there

00:16:47.430 --> 00:16:48.350 align:middle line:90%
and his mother went with him.

00:16:48.350 --> 00:16:49.370 align:middle line:90%
OK fine.

00:16:49.370 --> 00:16:52.280 align:middle line:84%
So now we can there--
I know one area

00:16:52.280 --> 00:16:55.570 align:middle line:84%
that you think for you in
this story is really profound.

00:16:55.570 --> 00:16:57.210 align:middle line:90%
We can jump right to that.

00:16:57.210 --> 00:17:00.290 align:middle line:84%
And that has to do with a
book by Nicolas Notovitch.

00:17:00.290 --> 00:17:02.560 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Yes,
Nicolas Notovitch.

00:17:02.560 --> 00:17:10.950 align:middle line:84%
We're back now in 1890-- wait,
let me see, I think 1887.

00:17:10.950 --> 00:17:14.520 align:middle line:90%
He was on an expedition.

00:17:14.520 --> 00:17:15.510 align:middle line:90%
He was Jewish.

00:17:15.510 --> 00:17:16.310 align:middle line:90%
He converted--

00:17:16.310 --> 00:17:17.110 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Russian.

00:17:17.110 --> 00:17:18.790 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: --to Catholicism.

00:17:18.790 --> 00:17:22.650 align:middle line:84%
And he's on an
expedition that takes him

00:17:22.650 --> 00:17:27.470 align:middle line:84%
to Hemis Monastery
in Ladakh, India.

00:17:27.470 --> 00:17:31.480 align:middle line:84%
This is around 14,000 feet
elevation, very rarefied.

00:17:31.480 --> 00:17:35.000 align:middle line:84%
It's a part of the world
that very few people

00:17:35.000 --> 00:17:36.690 align:middle line:90%
would get there.

00:17:36.690 --> 00:17:41.500 align:middle line:84%
And Notovitch had an
accident, fell off a horse,

00:17:41.500 --> 00:17:44.080 align:middle line:84%
broke his leg, and he had to
spend many, many weeks there

00:17:44.080 --> 00:17:45.890 align:middle line:90%
at the monastery.

00:17:45.890 --> 00:17:49.670 align:middle line:84%
And during that time the
monks confided in him

00:17:49.670 --> 00:17:52.850 align:middle line:84%
that they had an
ancient manuscript there

00:17:52.850 --> 00:17:56.380 align:middle line:84%
that told of the life of
Jesus that told of his travels

00:17:56.380 --> 00:17:58.130 align:middle line:90%
in India.

00:17:58.130 --> 00:18:00.800 align:middle line:84%
And he was shown
this manuscript.

00:18:00.800 --> 00:18:02.470 align:middle line:84%
Now these manuscripts
themselves,

00:18:02.470 --> 00:18:04.700 align:middle line:90%
they look very, very unusual.

00:18:04.700 --> 00:18:06.900 align:middle line:90%
I mean it's one page at a time.

00:18:06.900 --> 00:18:08.920 align:middle line:90%
It's like it's on leather.

00:18:08.920 --> 00:18:09.720 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:18:09.720 --> 00:18:10.020 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It was long.

00:18:10.020 --> 00:18:11.860 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Yeah, there
are these long pieces

00:18:11.860 --> 00:18:13.930 align:middle line:90%
one after the other.

00:18:13.930 --> 00:18:17.530 align:middle line:84%
But this book was called
"The Life of Saint Issa,

00:18:17.530 --> 00:18:19.970 align:middle line:90%
The Best of the Sons of Men."

00:18:19.970 --> 00:18:26.964 align:middle line:84%
And Notovitch had help in
translating it from Tibetan.

00:18:26.964 --> 00:18:28.130 align:middle line:90%
This was written in Tibetan.

00:18:28.130 --> 00:18:31.310 align:middle line:84%
But he was told
that the original

00:18:31.310 --> 00:18:35.200 align:middle line:84%
was in Tibet in the poly
language, an older language.

00:18:35.200 --> 00:18:37.700 align:middle line:84%
And the claim was that
this went back to the time

00:18:37.700 --> 00:18:40.410 align:middle line:90%
just after the crucifixion.

00:18:40.410 --> 00:18:43.960 align:middle line:84%
And it told-- it begins
with the crucifixion,

00:18:43.960 --> 00:18:51.660 align:middle line:84%
and presumably written by
traders from the east at that

00:18:51.660 --> 00:18:53.450 align:middle line:84%
time who heard of
the crucifixion

00:18:53.450 --> 00:18:58.790 align:middle line:84%
and then tell the story of Saint
Issa and his travels in India,

00:18:58.790 --> 00:19:02.880 align:middle line:84%
starting from the time
that he was around 13.

00:19:02.880 --> 00:19:05.590 align:middle line:84%
And those travels
they said took him

00:19:05.590 --> 00:19:09.370 align:middle line:84%
to Jagannath, that ancient
temple that would've

00:19:09.370 --> 00:19:10.780 align:middle line:90%
been about 500 years old.

00:19:10.780 --> 00:19:13.660 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Which is where some
of the top sages in the east

00:19:13.660 --> 00:19:14.700 align:middle line:90%
would have resided.

00:19:14.700 --> 00:19:16.290 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: Would have resided.

00:19:16.290 --> 00:19:18.110 align:middle line:84%
So the claim was
there in this story

00:19:18.110 --> 00:19:20.120 align:middle line:84%
that Jesus was in
Jagannath, like was

00:19:20.120 --> 00:19:25.020 align:middle line:84%
said in the Aquarian
gospel, which was supposedly

00:19:25.020 --> 00:19:27.703 align:middle line:84%
channeled information
from the Akashic records.

00:19:27.703 --> 00:19:28.510 align:middle line:90%
Who knows?

00:19:28.510 --> 00:19:29.280 align:middle line:90%
It's interesting.

00:19:29.280 --> 00:19:30.955 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: In that sense
it's all channeled.

00:19:30.955 --> 00:19:31.450 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: In that sense.

00:19:31.450 --> 00:19:32.440 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Every
book is channeled,

00:19:32.440 --> 00:19:34.231 align:middle line:84%
every divine work is
channeled pretty much.

00:19:34.231 --> 00:19:36.570 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: But
here's Notovitch who

00:19:36.570 --> 00:19:40.020 align:middle line:84%
is able to translate this story
and he wants to publish it.

00:19:40.020 --> 00:19:43.640 align:middle line:90%
And he goes to Rome.

00:19:43.640 --> 00:19:47.080 align:middle line:84%
He speaks to an archbishop
of the Catholic Church

00:19:47.080 --> 00:19:51.660 align:middle line:84%
who he refuses to name who
discourages him and says, oh

00:19:51.660 --> 00:19:52.910 align:middle line:90%
why would you want to do that.

00:19:52.910 --> 00:19:54.535 align:middle line:84%
Nobody's going to
believe it and you're

00:19:54.535 --> 00:19:57.030 align:middle line:90%
going to have so many enemies.

00:19:57.030 --> 00:19:58.830 align:middle line:90%
But he did publish it.

00:19:58.830 --> 00:20:01.900 align:middle line:84%
He also claimed that the
archbishop confided in him

00:20:01.900 --> 00:20:04.220 align:middle line:84%
that the Vatican knew
all about Jesus in India,

00:20:04.220 --> 00:20:07.280 align:middle line:84%
that they had many documents
related to Jesus' travels

00:20:07.280 --> 00:20:08.110 align:middle line:90%
in India.

00:20:08.110 --> 00:20:10.400 align:middle line:84%
It's not part of
the official canon.

00:20:10.400 --> 00:20:16.600 align:middle line:84%
This, like many of the books
that were considered heretical

00:20:16.600 --> 00:20:18.850 align:middle line:84%
and erased from the
record when they decided

00:20:18.850 --> 00:20:21.550 align:middle line:84%
what were going to be the
books of the New Testament

00:20:21.550 --> 00:20:24.129 align:middle line:84%
and the letters, and the
epistles, and that's it.

00:20:24.129 --> 00:20:25.420 align:middle line:90%
Everything else was eliminated.

00:20:25.420 --> 00:20:26.340 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Book of Thomas
eliminated, others.

00:20:26.340 --> 00:20:27.173 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: Destroyed.

00:20:27.173 --> 00:20:30.380 align:middle line:84%
Well, it was buried in
the desert in Egypt.

00:20:30.380 --> 00:20:35.810 align:middle line:84%
So Notovitch publishes the book
under the name "The Secret Life

00:20:35.810 --> 00:20:37.950 align:middle line:90%
of Jesus Christ."

00:20:37.950 --> 00:20:43.330 align:middle line:84%
And it causes a furor,
a sensation and a furor.

00:20:43.330 --> 00:20:47.270 align:middle line:84%
I think it was in
19-- no, it was 1894

00:20:47.270 --> 00:20:48.500 align:middle line:90%
when that book was published.

00:20:48.500 --> 00:20:52.130 align:middle line:84%
So this is what really brought
the Jesus in India concept

00:20:52.130 --> 00:20:54.472 align:middle line:90%
to the forefront.

00:20:54.472 --> 00:20:56.680 align:middle line:84%
But it got the attention of
so many important people.

00:20:56.680 --> 00:21:04.590 align:middle line:84%
For example Nehru, the first
prime minister of India

00:21:04.590 --> 00:21:07.465 align:middle line:84%
indicated that the belief
was very, very strong

00:21:07.465 --> 00:21:12.070 align:middle line:84%
that Jesus had been in
northern India and Kashmir,

00:21:12.070 --> 00:21:14.000 align:middle line:90%
Ladakh, that region.

00:21:14.000 --> 00:21:18.050 align:middle line:84%
So that gave it
further credibility.

00:21:18.050 --> 00:21:21.890 align:middle line:84%
In any event, there was
a skeptic or debunker

00:21:21.890 --> 00:21:25.980 align:middle line:84%
at that time, Max Muller,
who was a scholar.

00:21:25.980 --> 00:21:29.640 align:middle line:84%
I believe he was from England,
who attacked Notovitch

00:21:29.640 --> 00:21:32.890 align:middle line:84%
so bitterly, claiming he
made the whole thing up.

00:21:32.890 --> 00:21:34.580 align:middle line:90%
It was all a forgery.

00:21:34.580 --> 00:21:38.750 align:middle line:84%
So many Christians have
relied upon the debunking

00:21:38.750 --> 00:21:42.050 align:middle line:84%
of Max Muller to dismiss
this without knowing

00:21:42.050 --> 00:21:43.660 align:middle line:90%
the rest of the story.

00:21:43.660 --> 00:21:46.850 align:middle line:84%
The rest of the story is
fascinating, it's fabulous.

00:21:46.850 --> 00:21:49.860 align:middle line:84%
It's what gives it the
meat and credibility.

00:21:49.860 --> 00:21:51.530 align:middle line:84%
And it explained a
lot of our journey

00:21:51.530 --> 00:21:55.450 align:middle line:84%
in India, because for
us this was a quest.

00:21:55.450 --> 00:21:57.790 align:middle line:84%
If we could actually see
this document and proved

00:21:57.790 --> 00:21:59.490 align:middle line:90%
it still existed.

00:21:59.490 --> 00:22:04.160 align:middle line:84%
If we could even prove
the chain of those

00:22:04.160 --> 00:22:08.410 align:middle line:84%
who saw it subsequently
that that had validity,

00:22:08.410 --> 00:22:10.920 align:middle line:84%
what a contribution
we would be making.

00:22:10.920 --> 00:22:14.620 align:middle line:84%
And this is really what we were
able to do in this 4,000 mile

00:22:14.620 --> 00:22:17.140 align:middle line:84%
quest, not to actually
see the document.

00:22:17.140 --> 00:22:22.390 align:middle line:84%
We didn't succeed in that,
although we got to Hemis.

00:22:22.390 --> 00:22:27.100 align:middle line:84%
We have an interview with one
of the top monks from Hemis.

00:22:27.100 --> 00:22:31.340 align:middle line:84%
So we have an inside story
that hasn't been heard before.

00:22:31.340 --> 00:22:33.730 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: So
let's-- yes, go ahead.

00:22:33.730 --> 00:22:35.124 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: So here's the chain.

00:22:35.124 --> 00:22:36.290 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, that's right.

00:22:36.290 --> 00:22:39.910 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: From Notovitch
we go to Swami Abhedananda.

00:22:39.910 --> 00:22:41.850 align:middle line:90%
He lived in Calcutta.

00:22:41.850 --> 00:22:42.970 align:middle line:90%
He was a scholar.

00:22:42.970 --> 00:22:45.510 align:middle line:84%
He's written many
books, wonderful books.

00:22:45.510 --> 00:22:49.220 align:middle line:84%
They have a tremendous
psychology to them.

00:22:49.220 --> 00:22:52.590 align:middle line:84%
He's an expert in
Vedanta philosophy.

00:22:52.590 --> 00:22:55.690 align:middle line:84%
And there's still
a hermitage there

00:22:55.690 --> 00:22:59.480 align:middle line:84%
in his name with monks that
have kept his quarters where

00:22:59.480 --> 00:23:02.330 align:middle line:90%
he lived exactly as they were.

00:23:02.330 --> 00:23:05.574 align:middle line:84%
Thomas Edison visited
there in India.

00:23:05.574 --> 00:23:07.740 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, you have a
piece in the film on this.

00:23:07.740 --> 00:23:10.744 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Yes, he gifted Swami
Abhedananda his own gramophone.

00:23:10.744 --> 00:23:12.160 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I was
thinking we should

00:23:12.160 --> 00:23:13.560 align:middle line:90%
take a little peek at that.

00:23:13.560 --> 00:23:13.815 align:middle line:90%
Shall we?

00:23:13.815 --> 00:23:14.260 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: Let's see it.

00:23:14.260 --> 00:23:15.864 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Let's take a look.

00:23:15.864 --> 00:23:20.157 align:middle line:10%
>>And Swami Abhedananda lives
for about 20 years in America

00:23:20.157 --> 00:23:25.510 align:middle line:10%
and during that time-- 25
years, 25 years in America.

00:23:25.510 --> 00:23:30.420 align:middle line:10%
And then Swami Abhedananda
made a journey to Hemis Gompa

00:23:30.420 --> 00:23:56.620 align:middle line:10%
and found, he
was-- Thomas Edison

00:23:56.620 --> 00:23:59.800 align:middle line:10%
gave this to Swami Abhedananda.

00:23:59.800 --> 00:24:11.840 align:middle line:90%


00:24:11.840 --> 00:24:13.250 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: So that's fascinating.

00:24:13.250 --> 00:24:17.410 align:middle line:84%
So you wonder, OK what's
Thomas Edison doing there.

00:24:17.410 --> 00:24:19.510 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: He was interested
in Indian philosophy.

00:24:19.510 --> 00:24:23.420 align:middle line:84%
And Abhedananda had
a superb reputation

00:24:23.420 --> 00:24:27.150 align:middle line:84%
and he wanted to know if there
was truth to the Notovitch

00:24:27.150 --> 00:24:27.950 align:middle line:90%
document.

00:24:27.950 --> 00:24:29.340 align:middle line:90%
So he went to Hemis.

00:24:29.340 --> 00:24:31.180 align:middle line:90%
He was shown the document.

00:24:31.180 --> 00:24:37.990 align:middle line:84%
He translated it again, so I
think into Sanskrit this time,

00:24:37.990 --> 00:24:40.870 align:middle line:84%
so confirmation that
it really exists.

00:24:40.870 --> 00:24:46.200 align:middle line:90%
And that was in I believe 1922.

00:24:46.200 --> 00:24:50.130 align:middle line:84%
Following that up,
just a few years later

00:24:50.130 --> 00:24:55.575 align:middle line:84%
a great Russian explorer, an
artist, very respected man,

00:24:55.575 --> 00:24:59.810 align:middle line:84%
a remarkable man named Nicholas
Roerich leads an expedition

00:24:59.810 --> 00:25:04.300 align:middle line:84%
to that part of the world
and he gets to Hemis.

00:25:04.300 --> 00:25:07.280 align:middle line:84%
And he not only
confirms the document,

00:25:07.280 --> 00:25:09.710 align:middle line:84%
but he sends stories
back that get

00:25:09.710 --> 00:25:15.090 align:middle line:84%
to the top newspapers in New
York at that time, and in Italy

00:25:15.090 --> 00:25:17.810 align:middle line:84%
where it comes to the
attention of the Vatican.

00:25:17.810 --> 00:25:21.140 align:middle line:84%
And these newspaper
headlines there in our movie

00:25:21.140 --> 00:25:23.710 align:middle line:84%
and they're a remarkable
piece of history,

00:25:23.710 --> 00:25:26.620 align:middle line:84%
where the Western
world is being told

00:25:26.620 --> 00:25:32.620 align:middle line:84%
we've got a manuscript, ancient,
says that Jesus was in India.

00:25:32.620 --> 00:25:35.600 align:middle line:84%
Well, the Vatican
responded with skepticism.

00:25:35.600 --> 00:25:37.242 align:middle line:84%
Although it was very
interesting that--

00:25:37.242 --> 00:25:39.450 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, the Vatican
responded with skepticism

00:25:39.450 --> 00:25:41.040 align:middle line:90%
when you guys went to them too.

00:25:41.040 --> 00:25:42.170 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: Sure, of course.

00:25:42.170 --> 00:25:43.220 align:middle line:90%
It's their job.

00:25:43.220 --> 00:25:43.880 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's their job.

00:25:43.880 --> 00:25:44.990 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: It's their job.

00:25:44.990 --> 00:25:50.970 align:middle line:84%
But they did make a
point in connection

00:25:50.970 --> 00:25:54.740 align:middle line:84%
with their skeptical
response that they were not

00:25:54.740 --> 00:25:57.000 align:middle line:84%
questioning the
integrity of Nicholas

00:25:57.000 --> 00:25:59.742 align:middle line:90%
Roerich or his sincerity.

00:25:59.742 --> 00:26:00.950 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's good enough.

00:26:00.950 --> 00:26:03.160 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: But the
question is, if we

00:26:03.160 --> 00:26:06.580 align:middle line:84%
had our hands on this document,
science could study it and tell

00:26:06.580 --> 00:26:07.770 align:middle line:90%
us how old it is.

00:26:07.770 --> 00:26:10.880 align:middle line:84%
Now in the Hemis
monastery they said

00:26:10.880 --> 00:26:15.370 align:middle line:84%
this was a copy of the
original from Tibet.

00:26:15.370 --> 00:26:17.170 align:middle line:84%
You'd need the
original wouldn't you?

00:26:17.170 --> 00:26:22.920 align:middle line:84%
Because as the point is made by
Monsignor Corrado Balducci who

00:26:22.920 --> 00:26:29.870 align:middle line:84%
we saw at the Vatican, and
he was apostolic nuncio

00:26:29.870 --> 00:26:31.550 align:middle line:90%
of John Paul II.

00:26:31.550 --> 00:26:34.080 align:middle line:84%
He was a representative
in Washington, also

00:26:34.080 --> 00:26:37.050 align:middle line:84%
the Vatican's head
exorcist for many years.

00:26:37.050 --> 00:26:39.000 align:middle line:84%
And he kindly consented
to an interview.

00:26:39.000 --> 00:26:41.080 align:middle line:90%
We ambushed him.

00:26:41.080 --> 00:26:42.530 align:middle line:90%
We ambushed him.

00:26:42.530 --> 00:26:46.720 align:middle line:84%
He said, look he thinks
this is, he said in Italian,

00:26:46.720 --> 00:26:49.650 align:middle line:90%
"falsa, falsa, falsa."

00:26:49.650 --> 00:26:53.640 align:middle line:84%
Well, he said look,
in India certainly

00:26:53.640 --> 00:26:56.050 align:middle line:84%
they wrote this
manuscript after they

00:26:56.050 --> 00:26:58.440 align:middle line:90%
knew the full story of Jesus.

00:26:58.440 --> 00:27:01.470 align:middle line:84%
So he said he claims
it's an invention.

00:27:01.470 --> 00:27:03.450 align:middle line:84%
The Vatican doesn't
accept it he says.

00:27:03.450 --> 00:27:05.515 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: He forgets that
it would have-- well, I

00:27:05.515 --> 00:27:06.890 align:middle line:84%
guess it wouldn't
have pre-dated,

00:27:06.890 --> 00:27:11.950 align:middle line:84%
but it would have pre-dated
any text that they have.

00:27:11.950 --> 00:27:14.930 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: The problem
is if we had our hands

00:27:14.930 --> 00:27:17.860 align:middle line:84%
on the original text
and science could study,

00:27:17.860 --> 00:27:19.420 align:middle line:90%
they could really tell us.

00:27:19.420 --> 00:27:24.670 align:middle line:84%
Because if it was written 500
years after the crucifixion,

00:27:24.670 --> 00:27:28.070 align:middle line:90%
well why should we believe it.

00:27:28.070 --> 00:27:32.050 align:middle line:84%
Except it does mention
Jagannath as one of the places

00:27:32.050 --> 00:27:32.950 align:middle line:90%
that Jesus went to.

00:27:32.950 --> 00:27:34.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So this
keeps coming up.

00:27:34.200 --> 00:27:35.408 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: It keeps coming up.

00:27:35.408 --> 00:27:39.900 align:middle line:84%
So we went to Puri where
Jagannath Temple is, which

00:27:39.900 --> 00:27:42.280 align:middle line:90%
is a great center of Hinduism.

00:27:42.280 --> 00:27:43.560 align:middle line:90%
The original temple exists.

00:27:43.560 --> 00:27:46.640 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK now let's-- let me
just get to something before we

00:27:46.640 --> 00:27:48.160 align:middle line:90%
go there and set this up.

00:27:48.160 --> 00:27:49.990 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: Sure.

00:27:49.990 --> 00:27:51.490 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: James
Deardorff was saying

00:27:51.490 --> 00:27:54.720 align:middle line:84%
that Islam does
not believe-- and I

00:27:54.720 --> 00:27:56.530 align:middle line:84%
think this is kind
of critical to it,

00:27:56.530 --> 00:28:01.300 align:middle line:84%
they do not believe that
Jesus died in the crucifixion.

00:28:01.300 --> 00:28:04.571 align:middle line:84%
And this has been brought up
in other streams of thought

00:28:04.571 --> 00:28:06.070 align:middle line:84%
as well and other
schools of thought

00:28:06.070 --> 00:28:09.150 align:middle line:84%
that he didn't die in the
crucifixion per se, that he was

00:28:09.150 --> 00:28:12.720 align:middle line:84%
simply elevated from there
or suffered, was taken down,

00:28:12.720 --> 00:28:17.900 align:middle line:84%
and then left and moved on,
and went back in later life,

00:28:17.900 --> 00:28:18.810 align:middle line:90%
back to the east.

00:28:18.810 --> 00:28:21.240 align:middle line:84%
Where as we say the Mother
Mary and Jesus supposedly die.

00:28:21.240 --> 00:28:22.660 align:middle line:90%
We haven't gotten there yet.

00:28:22.660 --> 00:28:24.920 align:middle line:84%
So the point is not
everybody believes

00:28:24.920 --> 00:28:28.545 align:middle line:84%
he died in the crucifixion,
particularly Islam.

00:28:28.545 --> 00:28:31.620 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Well, what you've
just said about Islam is true.

00:28:31.620 --> 00:28:34.530 align:middle line:84%
But the trip to
Jagannath by Jesus

00:28:34.530 --> 00:28:38.820 align:middle line:84%
would be during those
missing years of 13 to 30.

00:28:38.820 --> 00:28:39.890 align:middle line:90%
So we're not the--

00:28:39.890 --> 00:28:40.270 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: We're not at that yet.

00:28:40.270 --> 00:28:42.392 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: --question of
after the crucifixion yet.

00:28:42.392 --> 00:28:43.350 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You're right.

00:28:43.350 --> 00:28:46.760 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: And what's
important is, well

00:28:46.760 --> 00:28:52.070 align:middle line:84%
when we went to Puri first
of all we were fascinated

00:28:52.070 --> 00:28:55.018 align:middle line:84%
by the fact that a hermitage
