00:30:33.510 --> 00:30:35.460 align:middle line:90%
We have subtitles.

00:30:35.460 --> 00:30:39.450 align:middle line:84%
But we asked him and
he said, oh absolutely.

00:30:39.450 --> 00:30:40.940 align:middle line:90%
Jesus was here.

00:30:40.940 --> 00:30:44.190 align:middle line:84%
He said you know the tradition
a Shankaracharya goes back

00:30:44.190 --> 00:30:46.750 align:middle line:90%
2,500 years approximately.

00:30:46.750 --> 00:30:50.610 align:middle line:84%
And Jesus would have met the
Shankaracharya of that day.

00:30:50.610 --> 00:30:55.600 align:middle line:84%
And he was here for
years studying with us

00:30:55.600 --> 00:31:02.440 align:middle line:84%
and learning the scriptures,
the Hindu scriptures.

00:31:02.440 --> 00:31:05.880 align:middle line:84%
And he listed what Jesus
would have studied there,

00:31:05.880 --> 00:31:10.190 align:middle line:84%
and that there was-- let's
see if I can remember.

00:31:10.190 --> 00:31:20.590 align:middle line:84%
But it was a truthfulness,
compassion, service to others,

00:31:20.590 --> 00:31:24.230 align:middle line:90%
patience, love, all of the--

00:31:24.230 --> 00:31:25.030 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Virtues.

00:31:25.030 --> 00:31:26.850 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: --all of the virtues.

00:31:26.850 --> 00:31:32.350 align:middle line:84%
And certainly patience is one
of the virtues of Hinduism

00:31:32.350 --> 00:31:34.450 align:middle line:84%
and Buddhism I
think, maybe more so

00:31:34.450 --> 00:31:36.650 align:middle line:90%
than what we have in the West.

00:31:36.650 --> 00:31:41.580 align:middle line:84%
But he could not produce
the ancient scrolls

00:31:41.580 --> 00:31:44.070 align:middle line:90%
that would have supported this.

00:31:44.070 --> 00:31:48.370 align:middle line:84%
He said that during ancient
invasions these were all hidden

00:31:48.370 --> 00:31:50.280 align:middle line:84%
and they don't have
access to them today.

00:31:50.280 --> 00:31:52.860 align:middle line:84%
But this is a
tradition that has been

00:31:52.860 --> 00:31:56.600 align:middle line:84%
known by all the Shankaracharyas
going back to the days of Jesus

00:31:56.600 --> 00:31:58.560 align:middle line:90%
that he was there.

00:31:58.560 --> 00:32:01.640 align:middle line:84%
Now this was the first
time I think in history

00:32:01.640 --> 00:32:04.280 align:middle line:84%
that a filmmaker had
gotten a religious leader

00:32:04.280 --> 00:32:07.220 align:middle line:84%
of this magnitude to make
those statements, which

00:32:07.220 --> 00:32:10.320 align:middle line:84%
were completely diametrically
opposite to what

00:32:10.320 --> 00:32:13.450 align:middle line:84%
we heard from Monsignor
Balducci at the Vatican.

00:32:13.450 --> 00:32:15.330 align:middle line:84%
And in editing
this movie I think

00:32:15.330 --> 00:32:17.920 align:middle line:84%
one of the key
points of it is when

00:32:17.920 --> 00:32:22.180 align:middle line:84%
I cut the two of them together
back to back saying completely

00:32:22.180 --> 00:32:24.610 align:middle line:90%
contradictory things.

00:32:24.610 --> 00:32:30.480 align:middle line:84%
Now the secret life of Jesus
the Christ, that document

00:32:30.480 --> 00:32:37.200 align:middle line:84%
from Hemis monastery, it says
that Jesus got into trouble

00:32:37.200 --> 00:32:38.624 align:middle line:90%
in his days among the Hindus.

00:32:38.624 --> 00:32:41.040 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Found that-- yes, I
found that fascinating, yes.

00:32:41.040 --> 00:32:42.623 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: It paints
a picture of Jesus

00:32:42.623 --> 00:32:46.320 align:middle line:84%
that is completely consistent
with the Jesus that we know.

00:32:46.320 --> 00:32:51.150 align:middle line:84%
It's not an all honey and
roses picture of Jesus there.

00:32:51.150 --> 00:32:54.270 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No, well, Jesus was
considered to be an activist.

00:32:54.270 --> 00:32:55.270 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: He challenged.

00:32:55.270 --> 00:32:57.145 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: He challenged
people, and certainly

00:32:57.145 --> 00:33:00.270 align:middle line:84%
the people in Rome didn't
care much for his ways.

00:33:00.270 --> 00:33:03.640 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Yes, well
he-- what he did was

00:33:03.640 --> 00:33:06.060 align:middle line:90%
object to the caste system.

00:33:06.060 --> 00:33:07.610 align:middle line:90%
You can't do that among Hindus.

00:33:07.610 --> 00:33:08.660 align:middle line:90%
They have four castes.

00:33:08.660 --> 00:33:10.326 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The Brahmin,
he said this is--

00:33:10.326 --> 00:33:13.650 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: The Brahmins,
those are the top people.

00:33:13.650 --> 00:33:18.270 align:middle line:10%
He objected to how they
were so aloof and put

00:33:18.270 --> 00:33:23.190 align:middle line:10%
themself in such a privileged
position up on a pedestal.

00:33:23.190 --> 00:33:24.890 align:middle line:90%
So he attacked the Brahmins.

00:33:24.890 --> 00:33:29.440 align:middle line:84%
And the lowest caste of course
would be the untouchables.

00:33:29.440 --> 00:33:31.150 align:middle line:84%
Well, you certainly
wouldn't read to them

00:33:31.150 --> 00:33:33.390 align:middle line:90%
the holy scriptures.

00:33:33.390 --> 00:33:35.887 align:middle line:84%
They'll get to hear the holy
scriptures when they come back

00:33:35.887 --> 00:33:37.970 align:middle line:84%
on their next incarnation,
if they're lucky enough

00:33:37.970 --> 00:33:40.440 align:middle line:84%
to be further up the
chain, but not now.

00:33:40.440 --> 00:33:44.162 align:middle line:90%
Well, he violated that.

00:33:44.162 --> 00:33:48.400 align:middle line:84%
He anchored them to the
point where an assassin

00:33:48.400 --> 00:33:51.950 align:middle line:90%
was hired to do away with him.

00:33:51.950 --> 00:33:55.390 align:middle line:84%
Now this is the story in
that ancient manuscript.

00:33:55.390 --> 00:33:57.810 align:middle line:84%
And it's completely
consistent with the Jesus

00:33:57.810 --> 00:34:00.350 align:middle line:90%
who in Judea in Israel.

00:34:00.350 --> 00:34:02.700 align:middle line:84%
He would've gone into
the temple and thrown

00:34:02.700 --> 00:34:06.080 align:middle line:84%
over the tables of
the money changers,

00:34:06.080 --> 00:34:08.389 align:middle line:84%
and saying not in
my father's house.

00:34:08.389 --> 00:34:10.809 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: He spoke his
truth wherever he went.

00:34:10.809 --> 00:34:15.080 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Yeah, it's
supportive of that.

00:34:15.080 --> 00:34:16.270 align:middle line:90%
This is fascinating.

00:34:16.270 --> 00:34:20.290 align:middle line:84%
Well, the claim is that then
he left and he went northward

00:34:20.290 --> 00:34:24.690 align:middle line:84%
actually to the land of the
birthplace of the Buddha.

00:34:24.690 --> 00:34:28.850 align:middle line:84%
I don't think I can pronounce
it, but as part of his journey

00:34:28.850 --> 00:34:30.179 align:middle line:90%
there.

00:34:30.179 --> 00:34:35.080 align:middle line:84%
So we had this confirmation
from the Shankaracharya.

00:34:35.080 --> 00:34:39.659 align:middle line:84%
What we really needed was
to get to Hemis monastery

00:34:39.659 --> 00:34:42.060 align:middle line:84%
and find out what's
their position.

00:34:42.060 --> 00:34:43.940 align:middle line:90%
Can we see the document?

00:34:43.940 --> 00:34:45.659 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You made it there.

00:34:45.659 --> 00:34:47.790 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Well we-- I
sent part of my crew.

00:34:47.790 --> 00:34:48.790 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah OK.

00:34:48.790 --> 00:34:49.955 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: I couldn't
personally go.

00:34:49.955 --> 00:34:50.739 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Part of
the crew, all right.

00:34:50.739 --> 00:34:51.699 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: As a matter of fact--

00:34:51.699 --> 00:34:54.210 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I didn't know if you
actually personally had or not.

00:34:54.210 --> 00:34:55.880 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: 14,000 feet would've
been a little tough for me.

00:34:55.880 --> 00:34:57.005 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Too much for you.

00:34:57.005 --> 00:34:58.729 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:34:58.729 --> 00:35:00.520 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Ed has climbed
a lot of mountains

00:35:00.520 --> 00:35:04.400 align:middle line:84%
and he really
wanted to go there.

00:35:04.400 --> 00:35:09.330 align:middle line:84%
But when we had been
to Kashmir, that

00:35:09.330 --> 00:35:11.510 align:middle line:84%
was going to be our
next destination.

00:35:11.510 --> 00:35:14.820 align:middle line:84%
We were going to fly to
Ladakh and go to Hemis.

00:35:14.820 --> 00:35:17.317 align:middle line:90%


00:35:17.317 --> 00:35:19.400 align:middle line:84%
Let me backtrack and tell
you what happened to us.

00:35:19.400 --> 00:35:21.980 align:middle line:90%


00:35:21.980 --> 00:35:27.120 align:middle line:84%
We heard that the plane we were
assigned to that we had tickets

00:35:27.120 --> 00:35:31.800 align:middle line:84%
for, that the prime
minister or the head,

00:35:31.800 --> 00:35:36.670 align:middle line:84%
the president of Kashmir was
going to be on that plane

00:35:36.670 --> 00:35:40.740 align:middle line:84%
with many people who worked
with him from the government.

00:35:40.740 --> 00:35:43.320 align:middle line:84%
And there had been multiple
assassination attempts

00:35:43.320 --> 00:35:45.630 align:middle line:90%
against him.

00:35:45.630 --> 00:35:49.880 align:middle line:84%
And the day before we
heard on the street

00:35:49.880 --> 00:35:54.500 align:middle line:84%
through the Muslim who
was part of our crew

00:35:54.500 --> 00:35:56.310 align:middle line:84%
that everyone on
the street seemed

00:35:56.310 --> 00:35:59.640 align:middle line:84%
to know that this man was
going to be on that plane.

00:35:59.640 --> 00:36:03.400 align:middle line:84%
And it was probably going
to be a target and somebody

00:36:03.400 --> 00:36:05.690 align:middle line:90%
might try to shoot it down.

00:36:05.690 --> 00:36:10.220 align:middle line:84%
So we decided, well we're
not going out on that plane.

00:36:10.220 --> 00:36:15.340 align:middle line:84%
Well we hadn't brought much
money with us to Kashmir.

00:36:15.340 --> 00:36:20.590 align:middle line:84%
We figured well we'll charge it,
tickets to get another plane.

00:36:20.590 --> 00:36:22.972 align:middle line:84%
First of all there wasn't
another plane out to Ladakh

00:36:22.972 --> 00:36:23.930 align:middle line:90%
that was going to work.

00:36:23.930 --> 00:36:26.060 align:middle line:84%
And second of all they
didn't accept charge cards,

00:36:26.060 --> 00:36:27.314 align:middle line:90%
and we were out of money.

00:36:27.314 --> 00:36:28.980 align:middle line:84%
We didn't even have
enough money to stay

00:36:28.980 --> 00:36:30.650 align:middle line:90%
in a hotel another night there.

00:36:30.650 --> 00:36:34.850 align:middle line:84%
We were on Dal Lake
in a houseboat.

00:36:34.850 --> 00:36:36.510 align:middle line:90%
We were really stuck.

00:36:36.510 --> 00:36:39.530 align:middle line:84%
We were there in the airport,
which was our refuge.

00:36:39.530 --> 00:36:42.080 align:middle line:84%
And we knew they were going
to kick us out of the airport

00:36:42.080 --> 00:36:47.020 align:middle line:84%
soon because we didn't
have a valid ticket.

00:36:47.020 --> 00:36:53.060 align:middle line:84%
Calls were made to one of our
associate producers in India.

00:36:53.060 --> 00:36:54.630 align:middle line:84%
And I think it was
a Sunday and he

00:36:54.630 --> 00:36:59.300 align:middle line:84%
had to get a banker he knew
to go into a bank on a Sunday

00:36:59.300 --> 00:37:03.680 align:middle line:84%
and wire the money to
get us out of there.

00:37:03.680 --> 00:37:07.980 align:middle line:84%
It was absolutely harrowing
because we were Americans there

00:37:07.980 --> 00:37:11.640 align:middle line:90%
and we were targets.

00:37:11.640 --> 00:37:13.300 align:middle line:90%
I went into a little curio shop.

00:37:13.300 --> 00:37:14.880 align:middle line:84%
We were trying to
use a telephone

00:37:14.880 --> 00:37:16.890 align:middle line:90%
to call this man in India.

00:37:16.890 --> 00:37:18.820 align:middle line:84%
And there were some
people who came in

00:37:18.820 --> 00:37:21.060 align:middle line:84%
and they sold knives
in this curio shop.

00:37:21.060 --> 00:37:25.190 align:middle line:84%
And someone picked up a knife
and was gleefully playing

00:37:25.190 --> 00:37:26.470 align:middle line:90%
with it and pointing it at me.

00:37:26.470 --> 00:37:29.700 align:middle line:90%


00:37:29.700 --> 00:37:34.140 align:middle line:84%
Could I be another little
notch on his knife.

00:37:34.140 --> 00:37:36.820 align:middle line:90%
So it wasn't fun.

00:37:36.820 --> 00:37:37.620 align:middle line:90%
It was scary.

00:37:37.620 --> 00:37:40.670 align:middle line:84%
So we didn't get to
Hemis on that trip.

00:37:40.670 --> 00:37:47.740 align:middle line:84%
Later I sent my assistant
director who is Hindu.

00:37:47.740 --> 00:37:51.260 align:middle line:84%
And he got the footage up
there and he got an interview

00:37:51.260 --> 00:37:52.390 align:middle line:90%
with one of the top people.

00:37:52.390 --> 00:37:53.860 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, that's the
one I'm referring to, yes.

00:37:53.860 --> 00:37:55.720 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Top people
from the Hemis monk.

00:37:55.720 --> 00:37:59.219 align:middle line:84%
This interview was
really curious.

00:37:59.219 --> 00:38:00.760 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Should we
take a look at it

00:38:00.760 --> 00:38:02.730 align:middle line:84%
and then you can explain
to us what this meant.

00:38:02.730 --> 00:38:03.530 align:middle line:90%
Let's take a look.

00:38:03.530 --> 00:39:05.900 align:middle line:90%


00:39:05.900 --> 00:39:09.930 align:middle line:84%
>>The lamas were not allowed
to open the archives which

00:39:09.930 --> 00:39:12.090 align:middle line:90%
are just bound with strings.

00:39:12.090 --> 00:39:14.490 align:middle line:84%
But the head lama, who
had given the orders

00:39:14.490 --> 00:39:17.120 align:middle line:84%
that they were sealed and
should not be opened until he

00:39:17.120 --> 00:39:18.120 align:middle line:90%
returned.

00:39:18.120 --> 00:39:19.870 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: What we knew
from that interview

00:39:19.870 --> 00:39:24.290 align:middle line:84%
was that they had many, many
ancient manuscripts there.

00:39:24.290 --> 00:39:28.560 align:middle line:84%
You could see them and
they're on these shelves.

00:39:28.560 --> 00:39:32.410 align:middle line:84%
And the lama explains,
well it's locked.

00:39:32.410 --> 00:39:33.590 align:middle line:90%
You can't touch that.

00:39:33.590 --> 00:39:34.910 align:middle line:90%
What does he mean by a lock?

00:39:34.910 --> 00:39:37.220 align:middle line:84%
It's not exactly what we
mean by a lock in the West.

00:39:37.220 --> 00:39:38.511 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: A lock and key, yeah.

00:39:38.511 --> 00:39:40.150 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: It's not
a combination lock.

00:39:40.150 --> 00:39:41.430 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't have a key.

00:39:41.430 --> 00:39:43.410 align:middle line:90%
It's a piece of yarn.

00:39:43.410 --> 00:39:46.510 align:middle line:84%
It's a piece of string tied to
hold the two doors together.

00:39:46.510 --> 00:39:48.640 align:middle line:90%
Why is that a lock?

00:39:48.640 --> 00:39:52.342 align:middle line:84%
Because it's been commanded
by their head lama.

00:39:52.342 --> 00:39:54.496 align:middle line:84%
You don't open those
until I'm back.

00:39:54.496 --> 00:39:56.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: He's been gone
for years hasn't he?

00:39:56.370 --> 00:39:57.350 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: Yes, yes.

00:39:57.350 --> 00:39:59.770 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No one knows when
he's coming back, if ever.

00:39:59.770 --> 00:40:00.936 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDS: Is he coming back?

00:40:00.936 --> 00:40:03.260 align:middle line:90%
He left as a boy.

00:40:03.260 --> 00:40:07.700 align:middle line:84%
And he was in Tibet and then
the Chinese communists come.

00:40:07.700 --> 00:40:09.560 align:middle line:84%
Do they even know
if he's still alive?

00:40:09.560 --> 00:40:13.620 align:middle line:84%
But they say that their
translation project

00:40:13.620 --> 00:40:15.212 align:middle line:90%
of the documents is held up.

00:40:15.212 --> 00:40:17.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Until he returns,
which may be never.

00:40:17.170 --> 00:40:17.690 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Until he
returns, of course.

00:40:17.690 --> 00:40:19.065 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Wait
for the next lama.

00:40:19.065 --> 00:40:21.650 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Of course,
now and the other thing

00:40:21.650 --> 00:40:26.680 align:middle line:84%
about the answer that
was so curious was

00:40:26.680 --> 00:40:32.680 align:middle line:84%
the person we were interviewing
said, look it's not up to me

00:40:32.680 --> 00:40:33.500 align:middle line:90%
to tell you.

00:40:33.500 --> 00:40:40.040 align:middle line:84%
I can't do this alone,
because this could involve--

00:40:40.040 --> 00:40:44.400 align:middle line:84%
it could be so sensational
that it would have

00:40:44.400 --> 00:40:47.080 align:middle line:90%
to be done by the committee.

00:40:47.080 --> 00:40:49.270 align:middle line:84%
It can't be one person
making the decision alone.

00:40:49.270 --> 00:40:55.500 align:middle line:84%
This could have repercussions
if we were able to confirm this

00:40:55.500 --> 00:40:57.620 align:middle line:90%
and I don't if we can.

00:40:57.620 --> 00:41:01.070 align:middle line:84%
I personally don't know where
the document would be he said.

00:41:01.070 --> 00:41:03.430 align:middle line:84%
But he said I have
heard the stories too.

00:41:03.430 --> 00:41:05.350 align:middle line:84%
He said researchers
have come here

00:41:05.350 --> 00:41:08.310 align:middle line:84%
who've said they talked
to the Dalai Lama,

00:41:08.310 --> 00:41:10.610 align:middle line:84%
and that the Dalai Lama
had confirmed privately

00:41:10.610 --> 00:41:13.390 align:middle line:84%
for them that when
he was a boy in Tibet

00:41:13.390 --> 00:41:19.870 align:middle line:84%
he saw that version of
the document of Issa.

00:41:19.870 --> 00:41:22.980 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The document that
Nicolas-- the secret life

00:41:22.980 --> 00:41:24.220 align:middle line:90%
of Jesus Christ.

00:41:24.220 --> 00:41:28.020 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDS: Yes, the
story of Saint Issa

00:41:28.020 --> 00:41:29.920 align:middle line:84%
that he sought in
the poly language

00:41:29.920 --> 00:41:35.230 align:middle line:84%
it would have been at the
Maribor monastery in Tibet

00:41:35.230 --> 00:41:37.900 align:middle line:84%
and that the Dalai
Lama was aware of it.

00:41:37.900 --> 00:41:40.910 align:middle line:84%
So the men we were
interviewing said look,

00:41:40.910 --> 00:41:43.510 align:middle line:84%
we can't say that this-- we
don't know where it would be.

00:41:43.510 --> 00:41:46.100 align:middle line:84%
Now I'm asking why wouldn't
they know where it would be.

00:41:46.100 --> 00:41:49.300 align:middle line:84%
Because when we know that
Nicolas Notovitch saw it.

00:41:49.300 --> 00:41:51.750 align:middle line:90%
Swami Abhedananda saw it.

00:41:51.750 --> 00:41:53.740 align:middle line:90%
Nicholas Roerich saw it.

00:41:53.740 --> 00:41:55.450 align:middle line:90%
Madame Caspari saw it.

00:41:55.450 --> 00:41:57.310 align:middle line:90%
We have two translations of it.

00:41:57.310 --> 00:41:58.550 align:middle line:90%
It exists.

00:41:58.550 --> 00:42:02.420 align:middle line:84%
Max Muller who debunked the
whole thing absolutely wrong.

00:42:02.420 --> 00:42:05.120 align:middle line:84%
And I wish all of the Christian
websites who are still

00:42:05.120 --> 00:42:07.600 align:middle line:84%
claiming that it's
a made up story

00:42:07.600 --> 00:42:11.590 align:middle line:84%
because Max Muller proved
that would back off and change

